    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "# Report on site health with HTTP / REST API and PostgreSQL without manual work\n\n**Pattern:** SEO Audit · **Level:** Foundation · **Trigger:** Scheduled\n\n## What it does\nReport on site health with HTTP / REST API and PostgreSQL without manual work. It runs automatically on a schedule.\n\n## Why it exists\nManual backlinks is slow and error-prone; this workflow makes the process repeatable, monitored and hands-off, with failures surfaced instead of silently lost.\n\n## Main flow\nWeekly Schedule → Init Cursor → Page Loop → Remove Duplicate Pages → Upsert Harvest into PostgreSQL → Tally Harvest Stats → Send Summary to Slack\n\n## Use it for\n- Teams that want to seo audit without manual effort\n- Anyone automating backlinks in marketing\n- Replacing a fragile manual process with a reliable workflow\n\n## You get\n- Removes copy-paste errors\n- Runs 24/7 in the background\n- Responds in seconds\n\n## Before first run\nConnect credentials: API key / bearer for the target API; Postgres connection; Slack OAuth2.\nFollow the color key: 🟦 entry · 🟪 AI · 🟫 actions · ⬜ utilities · 🟩 outputs · 🟥 error rail.\nEach node has its own doc card underneath — read those before editing.",
        "width": 480,
        "height": 900
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -830,
        80
      ],
      "id": "f6a168f1-7e06-82d8-8a03-65b8179e65cc",
      "name": "📘 Workflow Overview"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## ⏱ Rate limiting\n\nWork is batched and spaced with Wait so provider quotas aren't tripped. If you hit 429s, lower the batch size or raise the wait — throughput drops, reliability rises.",
        "width": 360,
        "height": 260,
        "color": 1
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -230,
        -20
      ],
      "id": "3db4abe1-c1dd-e1dd-1249-52232c987f3e",
      "name": "⏱ Rate limiting"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 🧹 Data quality\n\nDedupe/diff steps make re-runs safe: the same input twice will not create duplicate records. If you change the key fields, clear n8n's dedupe memory (node → 'Clear stored keys') before the next run.",
        "width": 360,
        "height": 260,
        "color": 1
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
